Latvian Premier Says Euro States Should Seek IMF Help, Welt Says

-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 
2011-12-07T06:56:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/latvian-premier-says-euro-states-should-seek-imf-help-welt-says.html
Latvian Prime Minister Valdis Dombrovskis said indebted euro-area states should seek
assistance from the  International Monetary Fund , Die Welt
reported, citing an interview.  Governments of  Greece ,  Portugal ,  Italy  and possibly  Spain 
should request IMF assistance that is tied to conditions to ease
their financial situations, Dombrovskis told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick Donahue in Berlin at 
 pdonahue1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  